From: Steven Kearnes <skearnes@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Preserve toolchain LDFLAGS when linking the PgSQL extension

The original `set(CMAKE_EXE_LINKER_FLAGS ...)` replaced the variable
wholesale, which on macOS clobbered the conda toolchain's
`-stdlib=libc++ -L${PREFIX}/lib -Wl,-rpath,${PREFIX}/lib`. With those
flags missing, the link found the wrong libc++ and reported missing
symbols like `vtable for std::__1::basic_stringstream` for the new
libc++ ABI tags (e.g. `[abi:ne190107]`).

Append to `CMAKE_EXE_LINKER_FLAGS` instead so the toolchain flags
survive.

---
 Code/PgSQL/rdkit/CMakeLists.txt | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Code/PgSQL/rdkit/CMakeLists.txt b/Code/PgSQL/rdkit/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/Code/PgSQL/rdkit/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/Code/PgSQL/rdkit/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -59,8 +59,7 @@ if(MSVC)
   endif()
 endif(MSVC)
 if(APPLE)
-  set(CMAKE_EXE_LINKER_FLAGS "-bundle -multiply_defined suppress"
-              "-Wl,-dead_strip_dylibs -bundle_loader ${PG_BINDIR}/postgres")
+  set(CMAKE_EXE_LINKER_FLAGS "${CMAKE_EXE_LINKER_FLAGS} -bundle -multiply_defined suppress -Wl,-dead_strip_dylibs -bundle_loader ${PG_BINDIR}/postgres")
   add_executable("${EXTENSION}${EXTENSION_SUFFIX}"
               adapter.cpp bfp_op.c cache.c guc.c low_gist.c mol_op.c
               rdkit_gist.c bfp_gist.c bfp_gin.c bitstring.c rdkit_io.c rxn_op.c sfp_op.c)
